ople do after they see them. So you can reach people more likely to take meaningful action, like purchasing a product.Â \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Meta pixel and iOS 15 update\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn 2020, the \u003ca href=\"/blog/ios14-updates\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eiOS 14 update\u003c/a\u003e made it so you are required to request permission to track iOS usersâ€™ data. The iOS 15 update continues this practice and has made a few more changes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Meta pixel used to allow you to see a 28-day click-through window and a seven-day view window. Now it only offers data for actions that have been taken within seven days of a click or within one day of viewing your ad.Â \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe aggregated event measurement system has also been tweaked a bit. The Meta pixel now limits you to eight events you can track per domain, which are automatically assigned, but can be customized.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe new iOS update has made data collection a bit trickier, but the Meta pixel can still get you the data you need.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"marketing-block marketing-block--light marketing-block--padded\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eðŸ’¡ \u003c/span\u003eTIP:\u003c/strong\u003e Want better ad performance? Use \u003ca href=\"/plus/upgrade?itcat=coreblog\u0026amp;itterm=shopify-plus-audiences-cta#Audiences\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eShopify Audiences\u003c/a\u003e to find relevant buyers and lower advertising costs with custom audience listsâ€”powered by Shopifyâ€™s unique insights from commerce data.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"22\"\u003eHow does the Meta pixel work?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFacebook used to have a custom audience pixel for retargeting website visitors and conversion pixels for tracking website conversions such as sales. While each advertising account had only one custom audience pixel, you could create many conve